cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD

This paper analyzes the distribution of publications and relevant citations by scientists within universities, measures the research performance of individual scientists, and provides performance rankings for universities. These topics are closely related to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SD (Software Engineering). However, since the paper focuses on bibliometric analysis and research performance, cs.DL and cs.CY are the most likely sub-categories.
